casebody.data:
Candice R. WEST, Appellant,
v.
STATE of Missouri, Respondent. ED 106591 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION FIVE. Filed: November 27, 2018 Lisa M. Stroup, 1010 Market Street, Ste. 1100, St. Louis, MO 63101, for appellant. Daniel N. McPherson, Assistant Attorney General, P.O. Box 899, Jefferson City, MO 65102, for respondent. Before Lisa P. Page, C.J., Philip M. Hess, J, and Darrell E. Missey, Sp.J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM.

Candice R. West ("Movant") appeals the motion court's judgment denying her motion for post-conviction relief pursuant to Rule 24.035 without an evidentiary hearing. We affirm.

We have reviewed the briefs of the parties and the record on appeal and find no error of law. No jurisprudential purpose would be served by a written opinion. However, the parties have been furnished with a memorandum for their information only, setting forth the facts and reasons for this order.

The judgment is affirmed pursuant to Rule 84.16(b).
